{
  "texts": [
    "Leveraging AI to navigate the expanding research literature for evidence-based medicineThe rapid advancements in medicine have led to an overwhelming amount of information that healthcare professionals and trainees need to process.",
    "PubMed, the leading search database for biomedical literature, presently has over 36 million articles and adds more than one million new articles each year [81].",
    "AI can help in medical education by quickly triaging and summarizing relevant articles, keeping trainees updated on new findings without having to manually sift through an endless stream of literature, and aiding medical professionals in identifying, synthesizing, and applying research findings [82,83].",
    "Due to time restrictions and a lack of expertise, medical students frequently confront significant challenges while practicing evidence-based medicine [84].",
    "The enormous amount of material to evaluate, along with the pressures of clinical duty, can be exhausting."
  ]
}